cs.NI, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the use of wireless mesh networks and radio transceivers for localization and tracking, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper presents a technique for generating 2D images of the electromagnetic field to detect and track people, which involves computer vision and pattern recognition. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper may involve machine learning techniques for processing the RSS data and improving the accuracy of the localization and tracking. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper may be relevant to robotics applications that require outdoor localization and tracking of people or objects. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper may involve systems and control techniques for optimizing the energy consumption of the sensing units and improving the performance of the RTI system.
